  <text>
      <body>
        <div xml:id="song37">
          <head rend="italic">A Dialogue betwixt <hi rend="roman">Cordanus</hi> and <hi rend="roman">Amoret</hi>, on a Lost Heart.</head>
          <head type="voice">For two trebles.</head>
            <notatedMusic>
            <!-- MEI goes here -->
          </notatedMusic>
          <div type="underlay">
            <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza" part="I">
                <l rend="indent1">Distressed Pilgrim whose dark clouded eyes</l>
                <l>speaks thee a Martyr to Love's cruelties;</l>
                <l>wither away?</l>
             </lg>
            </sp>
             <sp>
                <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Am</abbr><expan>Amoret</expan></choice>.</speaker>
             <lg type="stanza" part="M">
                <l rend="indent1">What pittying voyce I hear</l>
                <l>cals back my flying steps?</l>
             </lg>
            </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <lg type="stanza" part="M">
              <l rend="indent1">Prithee draw near<corr>.</corr></l>
            </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Am</abbr><expan>Amoret</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <lg type="stanza" part="M">
              <l rend="indent1">I shall but say kind Swain what doth become</l>
              <l>of a lost heart, e're to <hi rend="italic">Elizium</hi></l>
              <l part="I">it wounded walks?</l>
            </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <lg type="stanza" part="M">
              <l part="F" rend="indent1">First, it does freely fly</l>
              <l>into the pleasures of a Lov<corr>e</corr>rs eye,</l>
              <l>but once condemn'd to scorn, it fetter' lies</l>
              <l>an ever bowing slave to tyranies.</l>
            </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Am</abbr><expan>Amoret</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza" part="M">
                <l rend="indent1">I pitty its sad Fate, since its offence</l>
                <l>was but for Love, can't tears recall it thence?</l>
              </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
             <lg type="stanza" part="M">
              <l rend="indent1">O no, such tears as do for pitty call,</l><pb n="2A2v"/>
              <l>she proudly scorns, &amp; glories at their fall.</l>
             </lg>
           </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Am</abbr><expan>Amoret</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza" part="M">
                <l rend="indent1">Since neither sighs nor tears, kind Shepheard tell,</l>
                <l part="I">will not a kisse prevaile?</l>
              </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza" part="M">
                <l part="F" rend="indent1">Thou may'st as well</l>
                <l part="I">court Eccho with a kisse.</l>
              </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Am</abbr><expan>Amoret</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <lg type="stanza" part="M">
              <l part="F" rend="indent1">Can no Art move</l>
              <l>a sacred violence to make her love?</l>
            </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza" part="M">
                <l rend="indent1">O no, 'tis only Destiny and Fate</l>
                <l>fashions our Wils<corr>,</corr> Either to love or hate.</l>
              </lg>
          </sp>
           <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Am</abbr><expan>Amoret</expan></choice>.</speaker>
             <lg type="stanza" part="M">
               <l rend="indent1">Then captive heart, since that no humane spell</l>
                <l part="I">hath pow'r to graspe thee his farewell.</l>
             </lg>
          </sp>
          <sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Cord</abbr><expan>Cordanus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <lg type="stanza" part="M">
              <l part="F" rend="indent10">farewell.</l>
            </lg>
          </sp>
            <sp>
              <speaker><choice><abbr>Cho</abbr><expan>Chorus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza">
                <l>Lost hearts like Lambs drove from their Folds by fears,</l><pb n="2A2r"/>
                <l>may back returne by chance, but ne'r by tears.</l>
              </lg>
            </sp>
          </div>
        </div>
